commentPostTextItems.html: and the crowd invades the pitch!
Prasad caught in the midst!
as the crowd just lifts him up. Kokinos tries to protect Prasad and is mobbed himself
poor Prasad in danger of life as a happy crowd just toys with him
this is a crazy crowd out there
India enters the super six on run rate, ending the group at 2nd position
it is South Africa, India and Zimbabwe in that order
however, Zimbabwe goes through with 4 points, South Africa with two point and India with nothing in hand
Match State: India won by 63 runs
presentation ceremony
Alec Stewart receiving a cheque for $3000
Gavaskar asks him whether Stewart should have batted first in hindsight
Gavaskar also asks him a rather funny question: "where does England cricket go from here"?
Stewart just escapes that question with "we have New Zealand to play next... and so on"
Azharuddin picks up $6000
Azhar says he always knew Mohanty will bowl well in this conditions
and allowed him to bowl first
says he is not worried about Zimbabwe going through with 4 points
that he will have to win everything now
man of the match: Saurav Ganguly
Ganguly says he enjoys bowling here (in England), and brushes aside the way he was dismissed (runout from Dravid's stright drive brushing bowler's fingers)
